@{FG Shine}Welcome to AmiChannel News@{FG Text}

Hello and welcome to the 16th issue of AmiChannel News.

While I am writing this editorial, my CD is playing "Never be the same", one of
the biggest hit by Christopher Cross. I did not known until now that the title
of the song was about the Amiga. Yes, it will be never the same for the Amiga.

Although you will find very good (and better) information about the Home
Electronics World show (former Computer show) held in Köln in the reports
included in this issue, let me focus in the people who did not attended the
show.

For the first time, no Amiga Inc. representatives attended a big Amiga show. It
was not a surprise, as they are refusing to talk the community and they do not
have any product to show (the OS35 is a H&P's and Petro's product). Talking
about the devil, Petro was there, but he was not so optimistic about the future
as usual. Probably, he is fed up of the Tom Schmidt's and others incompetence.

Something similar happened with Phase5. The Oberusel company is in trouble
because Motorola is not supplying one essential component for its G4 boards.
Are the G4 boards another hoax? Who knows.

Village Tronic was neither in the show. As you probably know, they were
developing the 3dfx module for the Picasso IV. Although not oficially, this
project has been cancelled because they failed to port Glide to the Amiga and
they do not want to put more resources to finnish the port.

And what about the Mozilla port from Free Amiga Organization? Well, forget about
it. They were unrealistic. They had the 15 minutes fame and then dissapear.

But not everything are bad news. Wipeout 2097 PPC has been released. After the
Space Station 3000 fiasco, it seemed that Digital Images were not able to
develop the first Amiga game supporting both PPCand 3d acceleration.
Fortunately, the game has been released and it is probably the best game ever
released for the Amiga. If you have PPC and 3D card, please consider buying it
becuase you will support the development of other hing end Amiga games.

Another good news is the success of the OS3.5 sales, around 6,000 last time I
heard. But if we want a PPC port, H&P needs at last 25,000 copies sold. So
please, buy it in case you have not done it before. By the way, after the
release of this issue in Aminet, I will install on my A4000. Happy installing!

Remember to visit the SAUG website, which is located in:

         http://teleline.terra.es/personal/angelsau/index.html

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

         noticias@saug.org

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
Angel Alvarez - noticias@saug.org
Editor of the e-magazine AmiChannel News.
Responsible of the News Departament of S.A.U.G and Amiga Channel.
Member of C.U.A.E Nº 293 - FOREIGN DIRECTOR
