@node not05 "INFORMATION ABOUT THE DELIVERY STATUS OF THE G4 PRODUCT GENERATION"
       INFORMATION ABOUT THE DELIVERY STATUS OF THE G4 PRODUCT GENERATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Oberursel, 26.10.1999: Because of an unclear delivery situation of the Motorola
MPC107 system controller, which has been designed onto the Cyberstorm and
Blizzard G4 processor boards as the memory and PCI controller, the shipment of
these new G4 boards could not start by mid of October as earlier scheduled. As
there is no final statement about the availability by the vendor, we currently
investigate the possibility of using an alternative controller chip. If the use
of this alternative controller chip would be possible, the Cyberstorm and
Blizzard G4 processor boards would be shipped equipped even with an AGP port,
thus allowing to use a wider variety of the lastest and fastest graphis cards.

The evaluation of the technical features and the delivery lead times of this
alternative system controller, as well as the definitive availability schedules
of the MPC107 controller, will take approximately two more weeks until November
10, 1999. if the MPC107 can not be shipped by Motorola in quantities before end
of November, a shipment of the Cyberstorm and Blizzard G4 processor boards in
1999 will become very unlikely. If the MPC107 does not ship in time, and we
decide to use the alternative system controller, which is also a part of IBMs
Linux-PPC reference design, it must be expected that the Cyberstorm and Blizzard
G4 processor boards will start to ship early 2000.

As the add-ons modules are concerned, at this time the availability of the U2W
SCSI as well as the Fast SCSI II module can be confirmed. The current number of
back orders for the Ultra DMA ATA and the IEEE1394 module are yet not sufficient
to confirm the serial production.

All customer, who have ordered a Cyberstorm or Blizzard G4 processor board, will
receive a letter with a technical update and the new delivery schedules around
mid of November. Included with this letter we will also make an attractive offer
for the memory SO-DIMMs which are used on the Cyberstorm and Blizzard G4
processor board, as requested by many customers.
