@node not06 "PAYBACK STATUS REPORT: PART III"
                           PAYBACK STATUS REPORT: PART III
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From: "James Daniels" <james.daniels@apex-designs.net>

30 October 1999

This week(ish), I have been mostly...

   *...putting my A1200 into a tower. I quickly rediscovered that I'm
     definitely not a hardware person. Taking my beloved computer apart was
     pretty stressful, especially considering that it's my only development
     system. Thankfully, it all worked when I put it back together (well, apart
     from the audio mixer, but that should be sorted soon). Transplanting it
     into a tower has allowed me to fit a spanking new CD-RW drive as well,
     which will come in pretty handy when I need to write the gold CD for the
     game.

   *...converting the audio mixing code to assembler. This is taking a bit
     longer than I anticipated, but the results (so far) seem to be worth it.
     The assembler version of the mixer appears to only use up about 15% of the
     CPU's time, which means that the effect on the speed of the gameplay will
     be minimal.

   *...compiling the soundtrack. Several more bands have agreed to appear on
     the soundtrack. So far, nine artists have given permission, and have
     contributed a total of 14 pounding tunes. More details next update (and I
     really mean it this time :).

   *...getting a new domain name. Of course, you already know about this, but
     some people are still using the old URL. Please update your bookmarks!

Well, that's all for the time being. See you next time!

--
For more information about Payback, visit www.apex-designs.net/payback.html or
contact James Daniels at james.daniels@apex-designs.net.
