@node not09 "THE WORLD FOUNDRY: NOVEMBER UPDATE"
                    THE WORLD FOUNDRY: NOVEMBER UPDATE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From: Ed Collins <collins-e@dnet.co.uk>

1. TWF Opinion Polls

Two more polls have been completed since the last update.

The first of these polls, "What would your opinion be of a Linux version of
Explorer2260 ?" What a response that poll caused! There was a total of 258 votes
with the votes divided up as:

   * 192 or 74.4% - Good idea
   * 43 or 16.7% - AAGGH! Noo!!!
   * 23 or 8.9% - Bad idea

The second of the polls this month asked the question: "What's your favourite
control device ?" A total of 91 votes divided as such:

   * 45 or 49.4% - Mouse
   * 19 or 20.9% - Joystick
   * 15 or 16.5% - Neural Interface
   * 12 or 13.2% - Keyboard

A few complaints a mixed keyboard/mouse choice wasn't on the list. Oh well.
Can't please everyone.

The current opinion poll asks the question: "What is your favourite type of game
?" Fill in the form and let us know what games you like.

2. Explorer 2260 Update.

Here are a few of the things that have been done for Explorer 2260 in October:

   * More work on texture support and organisation (the editor now supports 5
     formats from 15 up to 32 bit)
   * Lots of networking research and testing. (Oh, the headaches!!)
   * Started converting sound library to PPC (now that AHI has gone PPC it's
     finally worth it).

To Do in November:

   * Improved texture handling for the object and entity editor
   * Add facilities to the display library to handle pre-rendered animations as
     well as realtime generated 3D ones.
   * Start work on the Linux server core.

The other news concerning E2260 is that we have decided to drop support for AGA
and make it a GFX card only game. This simplifies some of the development of the
3D game engine and from our recent poll has shown large support for this. This
will probably sadden and annoy AGA users which we are sorry about but the
decision is final.

3. Maim & Mangle Update.

Would you believe it! We haven't any news for M&M this month! Well very little
compared with other months.

Massi has had too many work commitments with his fulltime employment so could
find little time to work on M&M in October. He is now back working on M&M but
hasn't been able to settle on what is going to be done in M&M for November
(apart from dividing some of the GUI/sound programming work onto others). More
3D models have been done on the GFX front.

4. Next News Update

30th November / 1st December

More info at www.worldfoundry.com
