From: "Holger Kruse" <kruse@nordicglobal.com>

There will be no 'service pack' for OS 3.5 with an OEM version of Miami. As far
as the OS 3.5 distribution goes, the Miami demo is final, and I am no longer
involved in OS 3.5 development or support in any way. The organizations to
contact for anything related to OS 3.5 are H&P and Amiga Inc.

There is still the possibility that, if I have time for it, I will compile the
next version of Miami (3.3) in such a way that legitimate users of OS 3.5 will
not have a time limit when using the demo, as a courtesy.

However at this time it is not even certain that Miami 3.3 will be released in
the foreseeable future at all, because of my busy schedule, so there is not much
point in making such a promise. Because of that delay in finishing 3.3 I just
released "3.2b second edition" a few days ago, and later today or tomorrow I
will release localized versions for several more languages. I was originally
holding back these things because I expected 3.3 to be available much sooner,
but that has changed now. Don't expect 3.3 within the next 3 months or so. It
may very well take 6 months or longer.

In any case, even if Miami 3.3 is released any time soon and it does work with
OS 3.5 without a time limit, then this would still be completely unrelated to
the OS 3.5 distribution and any service packs, i.e. 3.3 would be available from
my web site, not as part of an OS 3.5 service pack.
