            VIRTUAL BALL FIGHTERS RTG DEMO VERSION IS NOW AVAILABLE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Virtual Ball Fighters is a new game in production by Italian developers, XTeam
Software Solution. They have just released a demo version of this game, which is
going to be published by Epic Marketing.

The game itself is in the Tetris mould, while not being exactly the same type of
game it borrows a lot from this classic. You get balls falling from the top of
the screen in packs of 3, all of different colours, you aim is to align 3 or
more of these balls of the same colour either in a horizontal, vertical or
diagonal line. Obviously, as in Tetris the basic skill of the game is to rotate
this marbles so they are placed to your benefit.

However, this isn't just it though, as there is one thing that makes it a whole
new ball game, the fact that its all against another player. The whole aim being
to defeat them, as with other games of this type, you have to try and make sure
there screen is filled with marbles before yours is. There are bonuses that can
help you on your way too including increase opponents marble speed, energy
recovery, decrease you own marble speed and much more.

The player has a choice of charactors in the game all of which have their plus
and minus points, although in the demo you can only play as Alice. There are a
number of different play modes for the player to select from. They can either
